      "body": "horizon commit: explicit-files form fails with empty error; --changed form hits a pathspec bug\n\nDuring session 0084-horizon-T12 (run 0010 context, ledger already at run 0013), `horizon commit -m ... <files>` failed with an **empty git error** \u2014 root cause this time is benign: the run-0013 integrator had already swept the working tree (`workspace[0013 r0] ground: integrate 0001-ground`), so the pathspec-restricted `git commit` had nothing to commit; the CLI surfaces that as `failed:` with no message. Suggest the CLI detect the nothing-to-commit case and report it as a no-op instead of a failure.\n\nSeparately, `horizon commit --changed` fails with `fatal: pathspec 'archon-horizon/events.jsonl'` \u2014 note the **missing leading dot**: it tries to stage `archon-horizon/events.jsonl` instead of `.archon-horizon/events.jsonl` (and shared state should be excluded from --changed anyway per its own docs).",
